⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Fyodor Pavlovich Karamazov
node BKZ · BKZ · ⟦Fyodor Pavlovich Karamazov:BKZ:a386a6⟧

WHO   — Fyodor Pavlovich Karamazov — the father · the buffoon-sensualist
WHAT  — The corrupt root: a neglectful father who fathered the brothers and abandoned them, rival to his own son for Grushenka, and the murder victim.
WHERE — BKZ · The Brothers Karamazov  Framework inputs: The Brothers Karamazov (Dostoevsky, 1880)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the novel needs a father worth neither loving nor killing — a buffoon whose death indicts everyone who wished it.
HOW   — By appetite, mockery, and money — and by a death whose guilt is shared far beyond the hand that struck him.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I was a swine and a buffoon and a bad father — and my murder made every son who wished it guilty, which is the only fatherhood I managed.

